(4) Pinned third-party references (wayback-pin pattern)
    For sources whose Terms of Service do not grant republication
    rights, this archive does NOT mirror the bytes. Instead, the
    archive holds a .custody.json reference manifest pointing at a
    Wayback Machine snapshot URL. The manifest carries
    bytes_stored: false to indicate the reference-only mode. The
    archive operator submits the source URL to the Wayback Machine's
    Save Page Now endpoint if no recent snapshot exists, and records
    the resulting Wayback URL in the manifest.

    The cardanocube.com content in this archive is preserved via
    the wayback-pin pattern. The TapTools content (from the Wayback
    Machine, pre-SPA snapshots) is preserved via the wayback-mirror
    pattern. The choice is per-source and is documented in each
    subfolder's README.md.

    For wayback-pin entries, downstream re-use of the captured
    content must respect both the source's license terms and the
    Wayback Machine's terms.

